From 3eebef039c67d1f2a424e92172ddcf6a7376072a Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Eric Koskinen <eric.koskinen@stevens.edu>
Date: Thu, 4 Jun 2026 12:00:09 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/6] Phase 3: loop-invariant SMT encoding in spec_generator +
 benchmarks

spec_generator.ml:
- loop_modified_vars: syntactic pass collecting base variable names
  written by a block; handles direct assignments, array assignments,
  heap-field writes, HeapAlloc (all three heap model vars), Decl,
  Havoc, and recursion into If/While/For/Commute
- While(guard, Some inv, body) in compile_block_to_smt: replaces the
  loop with its invariant via EExists/ELet over post-loop values of
  modified vars; exit condition (inv && !guard) under bumped versions
  pins each modified variable; SMT types from gstates or defaults
- While(_, None, _): explicit fallthrough (skips loop as before)

benchmarks/loops/ (8 new programs, all verified by CVC5):
- scan, countdown, stride, two-loops, reset: B loop does not modify
  the same variable as A; tight bound invariants pin exit values
- inc-loop, inc-dec-loop, add-const: B loop modifies same variable c
  as A; invariant uses local c0 = c (saved at loop entry in B) to
  express exact post-loop value, proving additive commutativity

test.sh: new benchmarks/loops section runs ./vcy verify on each file

